00:09:34.310 --> 00:09:36.120
effect you predict?
那些依變項的數值是根據預測所做的測量？

150
00:09:36.120 --> 00:09:39.035
For the dependent variable, it might be relevant to say,
依變項的說明清單可以報告

151
00:09:39.035 --> 00:09:42.617
I'm using a questionnaire and these are the items that I will average.
使用的問題選項以及要計算平均的題目

152
00:09:42.617 --> 00:09:46.168
And I will perform my analysis on this average score.
如何處理平均得分的方式等等

153
00:09:46.168 --> 00:09:50.375
It matters whether you do this, or maybe use one of all these items.
這些說明有關要不要做、該不該全做等彈性

154
00:09:50.375 --> 00:09:54.528
So this flexibility should be prevented by specifying what the DV is.
明確說明依變項的處置能避免這類彈性操作

155
00:09:56.723 --> 00:09:59.030
Finally, you should describe your analysis plan.
最後，清楚描述分析計畫

156
00:10:00.200 --> 00:10:02.308
How are you going to analyze your data, and
你要如何分析資料

157
00:10:02.308 --> 00:10:04.851
which statistical tests do you plan to perform?
要使用什麼統計檢定

158
00:10:04.851 --> 00:10:08.638
This includes specifying things like the alpha level that you want to use for
包括顯著水準的設定都要交待

159
00:10:08.638 --> 00:10:09.248
each test.
包括顯著水準的設定都要交待

160
00:10:09.248 --> 00:10:12.199
How are you going to correct for multiple comparisons, or
像是如何校正多重比較

161
00:10:12.199 --> 00:10:16.300
do you want to use a 5% error rate or a 1% error rate or a 10% error rate?
型一錯誤率設定是5%,1%或10%

162
00:10:16.300 --> 00:10:18.540
What do you think is sensible?
解釋為何如此設定是夠靈敏的

163
00:10:18.540 --> 00:10:21.670
It also requires you to specify things like data cleaning.
其他要交待的有如何清理原始資料

164
00:10:21.670 --> 00:10:23.230
What is an outlier, and
如何標記極端值

165
00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:26.080
how you're going to remove outliers when they're problematic.
以及移除極端值是基於什麼品質條件

166
00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:32.463
Now, we see that journals are increasingly starting to use these pre-registered
越來越多期刊開始接受預先註冊

167
00:10:32.463 --> 00:10:33.015
studies.
越來越多期刊開始接受預先註冊

168
