In this example, journal Perspectives on Psychological Science is using
以「心理科學觀點」為例

169
00:10:36.869 --> 00:10:40.847
pre-registered protocols to perform large-scale replication studies,
這本期刊接受大型再現研究的預先註冊

170
00:10:40.847 --> 00:10:44.639
where a lot of people team up and perform a pre-registered replication of
這是號召多人合作，進行主題文獻的註冊再現研究

171
00:10:44.639 --> 00:10:47.230
an existing study in the scientific literature.
這是號召多人合作，進行主題文獻的註冊再現研究

172
00:10:49.984 --> 00:10:54.735
There's a clear benefit of pre-registering your studies, especially when the journal
預先註冊有顯而易見的好處

173
00:10:54.735 --> 00:10:59.320
where you're going to submit your research allows for these pre-registered reports.
特別是有期刊接受你提出預先註冊報告

174
00:10:59.320 --> 00:11:01.250
So you can do this for a replication study, but
不只可以做再現研究

175
00:11:01.250 --> 00:11:03.770
you can also do it for very novel research.
也可以做原創研究

176
00:11:03.770 --> 00:11:08.150
This means that based on the plan that you have, you'll get comments from
這樣的好處是提出計畫之後

177
00:11:08.150 --> 00:11:13.160
experts in the field that tell you how to improve your study design before you have
你能收到同行專家給予改善設計的建議

178
00:11:13.160 --> 00:11:17.570
put in all the effort to collect the data, analyze the data, and write the report.
接著再收集資料，分析結果與撰寫報告

179
00:11:18.740 --> 00:11:22.130
Compared to the traditional system, where you only get all this feedback and
有別於傳統投稿模式，同行回饋是

180
00:11:22.130 --> 00:11:25.170
these comments after you already did all the work.
完成全部工作之後才會收到

181
00:11:25.170 --> 00:11:29.200
There's a big benefit because these peer reviews before you collect the data will
如此的好處是你在收集資料之前

182
00:11:29.200 --> 00:11:31.050
allow you to improve your study design.
就能根據同行建議改善設計

183
00:11:32.060 --> 00:11:36.590
So instead of doing all the hard work, and then being told by reviewers that you made
而非好不容易完成研究之後
你才收到負評滿滿的同儕評審

184
00:11:36.590 --> 00:11:41.100
a mistake or you should have taken into account something that you didn't see,
而非好不容易完成研究之後
你才收到負評滿滿的同儕評審

185
00:11:41.100 --> 00:11:43.920
you can get this feedback before you collect the data.
預先註冊讓你收集資料前就知道問題

186
00:11:43.920 --> 00:11:48.657
So this is a very efficient way to make sure that you perform a well-designed
這能有效地研究者獲得同儕審查的認可之後

187
00:11:48.657 --> 00:11:52.653
study, where your peer reviewers agree that this is, indeed,
執行良好設計的研究

188
00:11:52.653 --> 00:11:55.479
the best approach to study a specific topic.
這種模式對特定主題的研究特別有利

189
00:11:55.479 --> 00:11:57.764
And that the results will be informative,
結果不論有沒有統計顯著
也是有益科學發展的資訊

190
00:11:57.764 --> 00:12:02.180
regardless of whether they
are statistically significant or not.
結果不論有沒有統計顯著
也是有益科學發展的資訊

191
00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:06.560
And this is another very important benefit of these registered reports.
這是註冊報告的另一個好處

192
00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:10.123
When you've submitted your study design for publication, the peer reviewers
透過發表研究設計

193
00:12:10.123 --> 00:12:14.580
give you some suggestions to improve the way that you want to study this topic.
同行評審給予改善設計的建議

194
00:12:14.580 --> 00:12:20.790
The editor of the journal will say as long as you follow this pre-registered design,
期刊主編可向投稿註冊報告的作者宣言

195
00:12:20.790 --> 00:12:24.340
regardless of the outcome of the study, we will publish it.
只要如實按表操作，不管結果如何，必定完整發表

196
00:12:24.340 --> 00:12:28.085
Now, we know that publication bias is a huge problem in the scientific literature.
出版偏誤充斥科學文獻是不可忽視的問題

197
00:12:28.085 --> 00:12:32.696
There are way more study results that turn out to be statistically significant,
主觀預期經由很多方式引導發表的研究結果

